metadata.description:
"Take My Phone" is my second drop on Sound. Its also one of my personal favorite original songs I've ever written. 

Produced by: Alex Palmer & Sammy Arriaga
Written by: Sammy Arriaga, Aaron Scherz & Alex Palmer

Imagine yourself in a downtown bar surrounded by an ocean of people when you're meant to be having the night of your life but instead, you're sad, drunk and lonely. Your recent breakup turned you into someone you're not and the heartbreak has blinded you to it. 

This song is from my POV, putting you in my boots during my cry for help for someone to take my phone before I send the all the texts that I most likely will regret later on.

SAMMY

lyrics.text:
TAKE MY PHONE

We broke up on bad terms
Said goodbye with bad words
Trying to act like it don't hurt
But who am I fooling?
I'm with the boys in the city
Swimming in women and whiskey
When the lonely bug bit me
Shit, what am I doing...

You know what they say
Don't text your ex when you're drunk
Well, I'm one away from doing something dumb

Somebody take my phone cause
Imma start problems, Imma start problems
Take my phone cause
It ain't gonna solve em, it ain't gonna solve em
It's not like she's coming back
There's no way this won't go bad
The sober me would know that, oh

Somebody take my phone
Somebody take my phone

Every night at the same time
We'd fall asleep over FaceTime
Now I can't even face my
Bed if she ain't in it
I'm so scared to open my gram
I don't think that my heart could stand
Seeing her with her brand new man
Aw, think that I would lose it

CHORUS

You know what they say
Don't text your ex when you're drunk
Well I'm one away from doing something dumb...
